Job Description

At TOPIC, we work every day on innovative, high-tech solutions to make the world better, smarter, and healthier. Within this role in one of our internal projects, you will play a key role in driving technical innovation with a strong focus on your personal and professional development.

We are looking for a Senior Software Engineer, willing to relocate to the Netherlands. We are able to support you in the visa and relocation process.




“What I enjoy is the ownership and opportunity you get to grow.

Since our team works closely with our clients, you get the luxury of a familial company combined with high-quality high-tech projects. It is the best of both worlds”

Peter Barna | Software Architect @ TOPIC




What will you do?

Design, implement, and verify new subsystems, modules, and components;
Write and programming of maintainable code in Python for various features such as driver control software, human-machine interfaces, algorithm implementation, and/or UI application development;
Good knowledge of C++ or C,
Explore different solution approaches to achieve the best results;
Share your expertise to elevate the team, quality, and processes;
Collaborate with internal and external stakeholders in an international, multidisciplinary, and agile environment;
Review code and mentor (junior) engineers.




What do we offer you?

Challenging and innovative projects;
A focus on training and coaching;
A friendly and fun company culture with team outings and events;
A permanent position with a competitive salary (€50,000 – €70,000 per year);
An inspiring office environment in the Eindhoven area, with fresh fruit and fitness facilities;
Flexible working hours and hybrid work options for a healthy work-life balance.
Support with the relocation and visa process




Job requirements




What do you bring?

A Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Embedded Systems or similar;
At least 5 years of experience in software development with Python (plus C++ or C) in the high-tech domain;
Experience with O.O., UML, Unit testing, Agile, design principles;
You are a team player, solution-oriented, and proactive;
Motivation to continuously improve yourself and develop new skills;
A good command of English, and preferably Dutch.




Diversity & Inclusion

At TOPIC, we believe that diversity, equality, and inclusion are essential for innovation and success. We ensure a workplace where everyone feels valued and respected.

